Na5 12. Ng5 g6 13. Qh4 h5 14. Bxd5 exd5 15. b4 Be7 16. bxa5 f6 17. Nf3 fxe5 18.
Qg3 Bf5 19. Nxe5 h4 20. Qb3 Qxa5 21. Bb2 Rad8 22. Nc3 {Souza,A (2331)-Chemin,V
(2193) Curitiba 2010 1-0}) 8. Nc3 Nb6 9. Bb3 c6 {Consolidates b5+d5} 10. e4 Qc7
11. h3 {Prevents intrusion on g4} c5 12. Be3 {Black has a cramped position} Rd8
(12... c4 13. Bc2 $16) 13. Rac1 (13. Nb5 $142 Qb8 14. dxc5 $16) 13... Qc6 $4 (
13... c4 $142 {and Black can hope to survive} 14. Bc2 Bd7 $14) 14. dxc5 $18
Bxc5 (14... Nbd7 15. Nd4 Qc7 16. Ncb5 $18) 15. Bxc5 (15. Nb5 $142 {makes it
even easier for White} Nbd7 16. e5 $18) 15... Qxc5 16. Nd5 Qf8 17. Nxf6+ gxf6
18. Rfd1 (18. Nh2 Bd7 $16) 18... Bd7 (18... Rxd1+ 19. Qxd1 Bd7 20. e5 $16) 19.
Nd4 Qg7 (19... Rac8 20. Rxc8 Rxc8 21. Qh5 $16) 20. Rc3 Kh8 21. Rg3 (21. Rc7 $5
$18) 21... Qh6 $16 22. Nb5 (22. e5 $142 $16) 22... Nc8 $4 (22... Bxb5 $142 {
would save the game} 23. Qxb5 Rxd1+ 24. Bxd1 Qc1 $11) 23. Qg4 Qg6 $4 {Black
has lost his nerve... understandable when you consider his position} (23... Ne7
24. Nd6 Be8 $18) 24. Qf4 Qh5 25. Qxf6# 1-0

