win material: h6xg5} 8. Be3 O-O {Black has a cramped position} 9. h3 {White
threatens to win material: h3xg4} Bh5 {Black has a cramped position} 10. O-O c6
{Covers b5+d5} 11. dxe5 {White forks: d6+f6} dxe5 {White has an active
position.} 12. Qc2 {White has a very active position} (12. Nh4 Bxe2 13. Qxe2
Nxe4 14. Nxe4 Bxh4 $14) 12... Qc7 {White has an active position} 13. Rad1 Rfd8
14. Nh4 Bxe2 {Black forks: d1, f1+c4} 15. Nxe2 Nc5 16. Bxc5 Bxc5 17. a3 {
Controls b4} a5 18. Nf5 Bf8 19. Kh1 g6 {Black threatens to win material: g6xf5}
20. Ne3 Qe7 21. Nc3 Rac8 22. Qe2 Rd4 23. Nc2 Rd7 24. Rxd7 Qxd7 25. Rd1 {
White threatens to win material: Rd1xd7} Qe6 26. Na4 b5 27. cxb5 (27. Nc3 $5
$15 {should be investigated more closely}) 27... cxb5 $17 28. Nc3 Qc6 (28...
Qb3 $5 29. Ne3 Bxa3 $17) 29. Rd2 $11 b4 30. axb4 Bxb4 31. Nxb4 axb4 32. Nd5
Nxd5 33. Rxd5 {White can be proud of that piece} (33. exd5 Qd6 $11) 33... Kg7 (
33... Qc1+ 34. Rd1 Rc2 35. Rxc1 Rxe2 36. b3 $17) 34. Qd2 (34. Kh2 Qc1 35. Qd2
Qxd2 36. Rxd2 b3 $15) 34... Qc1+ (34... b3 35. Rd3 Qxe4 36. f3 $17) 35. Kh2 $15
Qxd2 {Black has a mate threat} 36. Rxd2 {A rook endgame occured} Rc4 37. f3 h5
38. Kg3 (38. h4 f5 39. exf5 gxf5 $11) 38... g5 (38... f5 39. Rd7+ Kh6 40. Rd5
fxe4 41. fxe4 Rxe4 42. Kf3 $11) 39. Rf2 (39. h4 gxh4+ 40. Kxh4 Rd4 $11) 39...
b3 (39... h4+ $142 40. Kh2 Rc1 $15) 40. Rd2 $4 (40. Re2 $142 $11 {and White
can hope to live}) 40... Rc2 $19 41. Rd5 $2 (41. Rd6 Rxb2 42. Rb6 h4+ 43. Kg4
Rxg2+ 44. Kf5 b2 $19) 41... f6 (41... h4+ $142 {and the rest is a matter of
